@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/privacy.css" />


<div class="policy-container">

    ```
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("dd MMM yyyy")</p>

    <p>
        Pharma Pulse ("we", "our", "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting
        medical store, customer, and transaction data. This Privacy Policy explains how data is
        collected, stored, and used when using our pharmacy management software.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Customer name, age, gender and contact details</li>
        <li>Prescription and medicine purchase history</li>
        <li>Billing and payment records</li>
        <li>Doctor reference details (if entered)</li>
        <li>Inventory and stock management data</li>
        <li>User login and activity logs</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Purpose of Data Usage</h2>
    <p>The collected information is used strictly for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Generating invoices and maintaining billing history</li>
        <li>Managing medical records and prescriptions</li>
        <li>Stock tracking and expiry monitoring</li>
        <li>Legal compliance with pharmacy regulations</li>
        <li>Improving software performance and security</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage & Security</h2>
    <p>
        All data is securely stored in protected databases. We implement security measures including
        authentication controls and restricted access to prevent unauthorized usage or disclosure.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do NOT sell, rent, or share your data with third parties except:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>When required by government authorities or law</li>
        <li>For medical compliance or audit purposes</li>
        <li>When requested by the pharmacy owner</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. User Responsibility</h2>
    <p>
        The pharmacy owner is responsible for maintaining confidentiality of login credentials and
        ensuring lawful usage of patient and prescription data.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
        Billing and medical records may be retained as required under local pharmacy and taxation laws.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Changes to Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Continued use of the software indicates acceptance
        of the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        For privacy concerns or support, contact the system administrator or software provider.
    </p>
    ```

</div>

<style>
    .policy-container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 40px auto;
        padding: 40px;
        background: white;
        border-radius: 18px;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
        font-family: 'Poppins',sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.7;
    }

        .policy-container h1 {
            font-size: 32px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .policy-container h2 {
            margin-top: 28px;
            font-size: 20px;
            color: #111827;
        }

        .policy-container ul {
            margin-left: 18px;
        }

    .last-updated {
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
</style>
